        <usage>&lt;DIV STYLE="text-align:Left;"&gt;&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Vertical integration simulates the field that would be produced by deeper equivalent sources. This transformation smooths data and is useful for source depth estimation and regional analysis.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;The process applies a 1/k filter in the frequency domain with stabilization to prevent amplification of noise at high and low frequencies.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Applications: Source depth analysis, regional field modeling, data smoothing.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</usage>
